				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You're correct that audio is far less <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Causal_system" class="postlink">causal</a> than video. Perhaps a better course is to patch the games' music engines to use a generic sampler chip on the cart, such as a Namco 163's synthesizer or perhaps an audio module ripped out of a Super NES and mapped somewhere in $4xxx instead of $002140-$002143.<br /><br />In any case, if you want to hear what music would sound like with the triangle waves replaced, listen to any Game Boy or Game Boy Color soundtrack. If you want to hear what music would sound like with both the square and triangle waves replaced, listen to any Namco 163 or TurboGrafx-16 soundtrack.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

